Structure of Story

1. ***Introduction**: Sets the scene by introducing characters and context*  
2. ***Complication:** Introduces the main problem for the characters in the story*  
3. ***Middle (Body)**: A Series of events and smaller problems that the characters have to overcome*  
4. ***Climax**: The pinnacle of the story, in which the characters solve a problem*  
5. ***Denouement**: The series of events where conflicts are resolved*  
6. ***Coda:** the optional part at the end where the moral is revealed*
